title: Employment by economic sector in Iceland 2019
summary: The given chart is of multi-line type with 3 lines namely Agriculture, Industry, and Services. The y axis represents Share of total employment and the x axis represents Year.
Overall Agriculture, Industry, and Services are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. Services, 2. Industry, and lastly, 3. Agriculture.
Overall across the Year, Services mostly maintained the highest Share of total employment when compared to others with a mean value of 77.39, and it peaked at 2019.
After Services, Industry overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 18.1, peaking at 2009.
Agriculture mostly had the least Share of total employment with a mean value of 4.52, which peaked at 2010 with a value of 5.59.
